item.title: Ricky - MAROON 5 - Moves Like Jagger ft. Christina Aguilera (Drum Cover)
item.description:
Ricky - MAROON 5 - Moves Like Jagger ft. Christina Aguilera (Drum Cover)
Hey guys it's Ricky Ficarelli with a new drum cover of Moves Like Jagger by Maroon 5. Besides the fact I've been getting requests daily for this one since its release, I totally loved the song, artists and the awesome 60's style video they did with Jagger. I really had a blast makin' this one, hope you guys enjoy it! Buy Maroon 5's awesome record on iTunes here!! http://itunes.apple.com/album/moves-like-jagger-studio-recording/id447628852 You can also buy it on AmazonMP3 here!! http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0059H09DC **Copyright Statement** This video is not intended to infringe any copyright laws in any way. This is for the sole purpose of entertainment; no profit is gained from this. It is the copyrighted property of its respective owner(s). Maroon 5 -- Moves Like Jagger from the 2011 release: Hands All Over is the copyrighted property of its owner(s). (External) Drums by Ricky Ficarelli RJF0811@aol.com Thanks again to all of you guys for taking the time to visit my channel and watch my videos. I appreciate all of your support, encouragement, emails, comments (most of the comments anyway... lol), suggestions and requests!! Keep 'em coming!! PLEASE SUBSCRIBE =D **MY NEW CHANNEL** Because so many of you have been asking questions about me, where I'm at, who I'm working with and what I'm doing... I started a BRAND NEW CHANNEL and invite everyone to check it out!! My New Channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/RickyDrumsTV PS: ** PLEASE SUBSCRIBE TO MY "NEW CHANNEL" TOO!! =) Follow me on Twitter at: http://www.Twitter.com/RickyFicarelli Visit me on MySpace: http://www.MySpace.com/RickyFicarelli My Website: http://www.RickyFicarelli.com My Kit: I am playing a Shine Drums, Select Custom Maple Series 12x9, 14x14, 16x16, 22x18, 14x6.5 White Sand Sparkle. My cymbals: are Zildjian "A" Custom, consisting of 14" hats, 16 & 18" crash, 10" splash, 20" Ride and an 18" china. My sticks, (what's usually left of 'em) are Pro-Mark 5B Audio Recording: The microphones I use are Digital Reference. I record using 7 drum microphones in all, consisting of 2 DR-HX1 Condenser mics for my overheads, 4 DR-STX1 Snare/Tom mics and 1 DR-KX1 Kick Drum mic. My microphones are run via 7 / 20ft Prolink Ultraflx Monster Cables into my interface, which is an Alesis io/26. From there it goes direct to my computer via firewire. For mixing and mastering I am using Steinberg Nuendo III. Video Recording: The videos are recorded using Canon 60D cameras and Apple Final Cut II for editing software. My Team: I have been blessed with some awesome people in my life and when it comes to getting these covers done... without the help of my friends, Bobby Keegan (Director Extraordinaire), Lucas Marchesani and my mix mystro Matt Feldner, it could not happen! You guys are awesome!!
